<TEXT>
his oncesolid support shaken by lurid 
courtroom tales of drugs sex and abuse mayor marion barry is 
finding comfort in the public embrace of black activists on the 
political fringe 
while the murky videotape image of barry filling his lungs with 
crack cocaine replays on the television screens and in the minds of 
his city washingtons mayor has been anything but reclusive 
he joined louis farrakhan the controversial nation of islam 
leader on a stage before thousands of people last week 
on sunday he bathed in ovation and song from the imani temple 
congregation of bishop george augustus stallings jr a flamboyant 
black priest who broke from the roman catholic church to form his 
own denomination 
barry also has appeared in recent weeks with rep gus savage 
dill a virulent critic of the white press even tawana 
brawley whose allegations of kidnap rape and defilement by whites 
were discounted by authorities after creating controversy in new 
york shared a stage with him recently 
hes trying to reach out to whomever will accept him at this 
point said linda williams a veteran observer of black politics 
and a fellow at harvards kennedy school of government center for 
press and politics 
many if not most of the standard middleclass black leaders 
in the nation and in the dc area are keeping their distance 
williams said therefore these are really the only elements that 
are openly coming to him at this point 
barry 54 is a former civil rights leader and street activist 
once considered on the political fringes himself he moved into the 
majorityblack capital citys political mainstream however and 
rose through elective offices to mayor where he is serving his 
12th year 
he now is on trial in federal court on drug and perjury charges 
that followed years of investigation prosecutors last week played 
the videotape of their hotel room sting of barry 
rasheeda moore a girlfriendturnedfbiinformer and a key 
prosecution witness has alleged she and barry shared illegal drugs 
more than 100 times and that they had a sexual relationship that 
ended when barry slapped her to a hotel room floor 
in a sideshow that has kept the citys radio talk shows abuzz 
farrakhan and stallings tried separately to enter the crowded 
courtroom at barrys invitation 
us district judge thomas penfield jackson barred both ruling 
that their presence could be disruptive and intimidating he said 
farrakhan is a persona non grata in the courtroom 
the american civil liberties union filed papers with the federal 
appeals court asking to overturn jacksons ruling 
in farrakhan barry has found an ally with whom he previously 
has been at odds 
farrakhan who has created controversy for calling judaism a 
dirty religion delivered a strong attack two months ago on 
local political leaders for moral corruption and said they should 
be replaced by muslims 
but last week farrakhan declared barry a repentant soul who 
is under attack and urged him to run for reelection 
during a break in the trial monday barry appeared before a 
crowd that gathered on a plaza across from city hall to cheer him 
also speaking was abdul alim muhammad farrakhans national 
spokesman who called the trial a subversion of justice and a 
lynching conducted because barry could not be defeated at the 
polls 
barry said in a television interview on monday that the crowds 
and farrakhans embrace at the rally last week have helped sustain 
him 
got a lot of spiritual feeling a lot of love there barry 
said about 10 to 15000 people cheered us genuine love that 
made us go through the night theres a lot of love in this 
city for me 
barrys jury is sequestered and thus insulated from the activity 
outside the courtroom but ron walters chairman of the political 
science department at howard university said i would be 
surprised if some of that didnt get to the jury in some way 
walters said barry is using the displays to tap a feeling among 
many blacks that he has been unfairly pursued by white prosecutors 
although barry has said he wont seek another term speculation 
persists that he might still run as an independent if he is 
acquitted or there is a hung jury the deadline for independents to 
file as candidates isnt until late august 
i dont think he has accepted that he is dead politically 
williams said 
