<TEXT>
pointing to a map of lebanons 
coast the captain of the israeli patrol boat dvora says the 
possibility of a palestinian guerrilla attack has seldom been 
greater 
in the eight years i have been on these boats i dont 
remember a time when there was such certainty in the air that 
something was going to happen said capt chen 
he spoke as the 69foot craft sliced through the waters a few 
hundred yards off the south lebanon coast sweeping the coastline 
with radar and occasionally stabbing through the darkness with a 
powerful searchlight 
the tension felt by chen and his eightmember crew is reflected 
throughout israel at a time when efforts to arrange 
palestinianisraeli negotiations are at a standstill 
palestinian guerrillas including hardliners who oppose plo 
chairman yasser arafats diplomatic initiative have mounted two 
recent seaborne raids using speedboats for the first time and 
finding a chink in israels armor 
on the jewish holiday of shavuot on may 30 boats with heavily 
armed palestinians from abul abbas palestine liberation front were 
launched from a mother ship that had set sail from libya 
one outran israeli defenders and reached the shore near a 
crowded beach resort before four arabs were killed and seven 
captured the attack prompted the united states to suspend its 
political dialogue with the plo 
on june 23 chens dvora bee in hebrew ran down a speedboat 
heading toward the israeli border settlement of rosh haniqra and 
killed two guerrillas armed with rocketpropelled grenades and 
automatic rifles responsibility was claimed by a fundamentalist 
faction of lebanese sunni moslems traditional allies of the plo 
ariel merari a terror expert at tel aviv university says a 
successful raid could set off a chain reaction that could end in a 
new middle east war he notes that terror raids were a contributing 
factor to the 1956 1967 and 1982 wars between israel and its arab 
neighbors 
a single dramatic terror attack or series of smaller ones 
change the atmosphere and trigger a war he said 
for example he said if abul abbas heavily armed guerrillas 
had slain israelis on beaches and in hotels as reportedly planned 
the public outcry in israel would have made it necessary for the 
government to carry out a spectacular retaliatory strike i 
presume against libya 
that in turn could have prompted iraqs saddam hussein to make 
good on pledges to help arab states attacked by israel 
at night along the rocky coast of south lebanon the defense 
against guerrilla raids seems fragile indeed 
the israeli craft based on a us patrol boat designed for 
vietnams mekong river seems to have little more firepower and 
speed than most of its guerrilla adversaries 
its weaponry consists mainly of world war iiera 20mm cannons 
and light machine guns plus some rocketfired munitions its top 
speed is about 40 knots 
its like soccer we cant let them get past us and head for 
the goal explained chen who spent much of a recent night 
hunched over trying to sort out suspect ships from birds waves 
and friendlies on a platesized radar screen swarming with a 
rorschach of dots 
chen whose full name could not be used in keeping with military 
regulations was surrounded by a bank of squawking radios linking 
him to other israeli patrol craft as well as radar and other shore 
installations 
overriding everything however is the driving beat of wont 
back down a tom petty song being played by israels armed forces 
radio 
the crew breaks the boredom by microwaving a series of snacks 
including pizza and a soybean chicken substitute made in a factory 
on chens kibbutz in northern israel 
about 330 am a bell sounds for battle stations and the crew 
scrambles from the airconditioned bunkrooms to the slippery decks 
of the lurching and rolling dvora 
moments later they stand down it was just a flock of birds 
said eldad a crew member who was steering the craft on the exposed 
fly bridge within rifle range of the coast 
the jumpiness is both an outgrowth of the proximity to israels 
border and the variety of threats the guerrillas pose 
chen said guerrillas have tried to sneak past israeli defenses 
by sending lone frogmen underwater or rubber dinghies that hug the 
shore line and are difficult to see with nightvision scopes and 
radar they have also planted mines or tried suicide attacks 
the political situation is such that the palestinians are 
returning to the use of arms they are trying from the shore from 
the sea and from the air he said 
