<DOCNO> AP900703-0030 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
each year hundreds of thousands of moslems from around the 
world travel to the holy city of mecca by land sea or even on foot 
for the annual pilgrimage known as the hajj it is the worlds 
largest religious gathering 
the pilgrimage to islams holiest shrines in saudi arabia brings 
together arabian princes merchants from indonesia peasants from 
soviet uzbekistan and paupers from bangladesh 
the hajj must be made at least once in a lifetime by all moslems 
who can afford it a moslem who performs the pilgrimage is called a 
hajji 
during the hajj pilgrims must abstain from sex and may not 
quarrel cut their hair or even kill a fly 
hajjis start the pilgrimage by praying at the grand mosque in 
mecca they then circle seven times around the kaaba a granite 
cube draped with goldembroidered black brocade moslems honor the 
kaaba as the house of allah where the prophet abraham offered his 
first prayers to god 
hajjis are then required to run back and forth seven times 
between two rocks about halfamile apart called alsafa and 
almarwa this ceremony is meant to relive the agony of hagar 
abrahams second wife when she was looking for water for her son 
ishmael considered the ancestor of the arabs 
the main center of the pilgrimage then moves to mina a meeting 
place for the hajjis to gather before they climb mount arafat for 
the climax of the observances moslems believe arafat is where 
abraham showed his devotion to god by offering to sacrifice his son 
at mount arafat each pilgrim throws seven stones at each of the 
three devil pillars a spot where moslems believe the devil 
tried to tempt abraham to disobey allah and refuse to sacrifice his 
son at twilight pilgrims offer the eid aladha or feast of 
sacrifice prayers before slaughtering hundreds of thousands of 
sheep cows and camels 
over the years the hajj has been beset by tragedy 
in 1979 religious extremists seized the grand mosque in mecca 
and held it for two weeks before saudi forces stormed it more than 
250 people were killed and saudi authorities later beheaded 63 more 
in 1987 clashes with saudi security forces in mecca killed 402 
people during the hajj 275 of them iranians it was the most 
serious of a series of incidents during pilgrimages since irans 
1979 islamic revolution 
after that carnage saudi arabia restricted the number of 
pilgrims and later broke off diplomatic ties with iran 
the incidents were fired by iranian efforts to politicize the 
hajj and encourage other moslem nations to seize shrines at mecca 
and medina from the control of the kingdoms saud royal family 
iran denied in september 1989 that it was involved in two bomb 
blasts in mecca two months earlier and tehransupported terrorists 
vowed to avenge saudi arabias execution of 16 shiite moslems 
convicted of setting the explosions 
the bombs exploded as thousands of people took part in the hajj 
killing one person and injuring 16 
the attacks were believed connected to the centuriesold feud 
between sunni and shiite moslems the saudi royal family is sunni 
while shiites are an overwhelming majority among irans nearly 50 
million people 
last year an estimated 18 million moslems from more than 80 
nations went on the annual pilgrimage an estimated 2 million 
people attended this year 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

