<TEXT>
the fall and winter brought east 
germanys revolution summer saw the economic merger of the two 
germanys now people are predicting a hot autumn as the two 
states stride toward political unity 
so far the moves toward unification have been charged with 
symbolism the tearing down of the berlin wall the establishment 
of a single currency the elimination of internal border controls 
the next stage looks to be more prosaic long and difficult 
negotiations toward the political treaty that will iron out 
constitutional and legal obstacles to unification 
government negotiators hope to be able to present a unity treaty 
to their respective parliaments in september 
on monday night the east german government called for joint 
elections in both countries on dec 2 one of two december dates 
proposed by the bonn government 
guenther krause a leader of east germanys dominant christian 
democratic union said the east german proposal also calls for 
state elections in east germany on oct 14 
officials in bonn have said they want to change only those parts 
of the west german constitution absolutely necessary for 
unification 
but one of the biggest legal differences between the two 
germanys their opposing abortion laws will probably be left 
unresolved before unification 
in west germany a woman must prove medical or financial 
necessity to have an abortion in east germany abortions on demand 
are legal in the first trimester 
a west german government spokesman speaking on condition of 
anonymity said the differing laws would probably continue for a 
transitional period meaning west german women could travel east 
for abortions 
another point of contention is what city berlin or bonn will 
be the capital of a united germany 
east german prime minister lothar de maiziere has said he wants 
berlin stipulated as the capital in the final unification treaty 
but politicians in the west have balked and kohls government has 
said the decision must come from a united german parliament 
how to conduct allgerman elections for a united parliament has 
also become a point of debate 
west german law requires political parties to have a minimum 5 
percent election showing for representation in parliament there is 
no such minimum in east germany and politicians there have said it 
would be unfair to require east german parties to attain 5 percent 
of the vote in a united germany 
as a compromise west german interior minister wolfgang 
schaeuble has suggested that the balloting be conducted separately 
in east and west germany 
domestic financial issues also need resolving 
east german finance minister walter romberg has demanded 
negotiations to include east germany in a west german financial 
program that redistributes funds from rich areas to poorer ones 
but according to a west german draft of the unity treaty the 
five new states in what is now east germany would not be eligible 
for such revenuesharing until after 1994 
the 70 billion german unity fund established to help with east 
german reconstruction would be the sole source of financing until 
then the draft says 
unification is also contingent on international approval but 
that is expected to come in november at a meeting of the 35nation 
conference on security and cooperation in europe 
last week west germany addressed some of moscows concerns 
about german unification by announcing that 780 million would go 
to help finance the cost of the 380000 soviet troops in east 
germany for the second half of 1990 
the status of soviet troops in east germany the military 
posture of a united germany and the size of a combined german army 
have been the kremlins main worries about a reunited germany 
the soviets have opposed a united germanys membership in nato 
but chancellor helmut kohl plans to visit moscow july 1516 for 
talks that are expected to focus on winning soviet approval for 
german nato membership by providing western aid to the moribund 
soviet economy 
west germany has already backed a 3 billion bank credit to the 
soviet union and has been pressing the european economic community 
to support an even larger aid package 
