announced monday by massachusetts institute of technology where he 
was a professor emeritus in electrical engineering 
licklider was among the first to recognize that the full 
potential of computers could be reached only by improving users 
ability to interact with them he believed computers need not only 
be used to generate information 
his views were supported by the defense departments advanced 
research projects agency which established largescale 
experimental computer science research projects at universities 
around the country 
licklider headed the first one project mac from 1968 to 1970 
it now is the mit laboratory for computer science 
he contributed to the application of computers in libraries 
introducing the concepts of digital computers and 
telecommunications into the processes of storing and retrieving 
information 
