lloyd w hazleton founder of hazleton 
laboratories one of the worlds largest biological testing 
services has died 
hazleton 79 died of cancer saturday at his mclean home 
hazleton who had a doctorate in pharmacology founded the 
biotechnology research company with his wife harriet rosenzweig 
hazleton in 1946 on the grounds of an old country schoolhouse in 
fairfax 
the company originally known as hazleton laboratories america 
inc became one of the worlds largest biological testing 
services doing pretests of new chemicals for virtually every 
major chemical cosmetic and pharmaceutical manufacturer 
he sold the company in 1968 and retired as president the 
company is now known as the hazleton corp and is based in herndon 
va 
hazleton a native of washington state moved to the washington 
dc area in 1939 when he joined the faculty of georgetown 
university medical school as a pharmacology professor he left 
georgetown two years later and taught at george washington until he 
founded hazleton laboratories 
his first wife harriet hazleton died in 1986 
survivors include his wife grace murphy hazleton three 
children a sister and six grandchildren 
