public school teachers earn the highest salaries 
in alaska and the lowest in south dakota according to a survey 
that put the national average at 31315 
the average salary for us public school teachers in 198990 
rose 57 percent from a year ago said the survey issued monday at 
the annual convention of the 744000member american federation of 
teachers 
alaska had the highest average salary 43097 south dakota the 
lowest 21300 
average teacher salaries are nearly double 1980 levels of 
16100 and more than triple the 9705 earned in 1972 but after 
adjusting for inflation salaries have gone up a scant 68 a year 
since 1972 the survey said 
the statistics covered pay rates for the regular school year 
excluding extra pay for such things as working during the summer or 
supervising extracurricular activities 
teacher salary increases exceeded inflation for the eighth 
straight year and average starting salaries topped 20000 for the 
first time aft research director jewell gould told reporters today 
but starting teacher pay remains 5000 to 10000 below most 
other professions gould said starting engineers for example 
earn 32304 on average according to the union statistics liberal 
arts majors average 26244 and beginning accountants average 
27408 
with the lousy working conditions most teachers face and the 
lower salary levels its no wonder people are choosing other 
professions said aft president albert shanker 
teacher pay lags behind that of most other professions he said 
