23 as he and three friends walked through the south brooklyn 
neighborhood of bensonhurst the four blacks crossed paths with a 
gang of batwielding whites which vento allegedly helped organize 
the attack was widely viewed as one of the worst racial 
incidents in new york in years the murder was a shock for a city 
trying to heal from the wounds of the racial killing in another 
predominantly white neighborhood howard beach as well as 
allegations of police attacks on blacks and other racially charged 
incidents in the late 1980s 
fama named as the triggerman by several of the defendants was 
sentenced to 32 and twothirds years to life ringleader mondello 
19 was acquitted of homicide charges but sentenced to five and 
onethird to 16 years in prison for his other convictions 
five other young bensonhurst whites accused of being part of the 
mob are to stand trial later 
the day after hawkins murder vento fled upstate but he soon 
called prosecutors to admit his role he also agreed to cooperate 
in the investigation and to testify against his friends in exchange 
for immunity from prosecution 
when he appeared before a grand jury in september vento gave a 
complete and graphic account of the attack he said he watched from 
just several feet away as fama pulled an automatic pistol and fired 
into hawkins chest 
vento told of seeing the sparks coming out of the gun pop 
the fire as hawkins collapsed to the sidewalk fatally wounded 
the whites ran without stopping to help him 
around christmas with the scheduled start of the first 
bensonhurst trial a little more than two months away vento again 
fled the city he surrendered to fbi agents in dayton ohio in 
march but announced he would no longer cooperate he was indicted 
by a grand jury a week later 
while theres no evidence vento even touched a gun the night of 
shooting prosecutors accused him of being a key player who helped 
his friend mondello call together the gang 
like a good general john vento marshals his troops just 
before the fray assistant district attorney martin hershey said 
in his final arguments 
vento was as guilty of murder as the shooter prosecutors 
charged because he continued to pursue the blacks after hearing 
fama say he was going to shoot one of them 
but defense lawyer gerald dichiara said fama acted independently 
and without warning in killing hawkins he also accused prosecutors 
of creating a racial issue for political purposes and going after 
vento out of vengeance because he reneged on his agreement to 
testify against the others 
