the picture computer processing would recover less than 50 percent 
of the visual photo science that was expected from the 15 billion 
telescope 
hubbles basic problem is that a mistake was made in the 
grinding and polishing of either the primary or the secondary 
mirror on the telescope weiler said one of the reflecting surfaces 
was not cut to the correct prescription and as a result the two 
mirrors do not work together properly 
the result is a fuzzy view of the universe from the telescope 
