nevertheless richards and other analysts said the factory 
orders report was the latest of several suggesting the 
manufacturing slump may be about to reverse itself 
orders for durable goods bigticket items expected to last at 
least three years jumped 40 percent to 1286 billion nearly 
recovering the 41 percent decline in april 
the often volatile defense orders also rose up 192 percent to 
100 billion after gains of 48 percent and 45 percent excluding 
the defense category orders were up 15 percent 
