american slaves who had ruled the west african country for more 
than a century 
doe initially won wide support but subsequently was accused of 
brutal oppression of critics suppressing the countrys free press 
and mismanagement and corruption 
the rebels of the national patriotic front invaded liberia 
from the ivory coast dec 24 sweeping across the country with 
little resistance from does forces 
government troops were accused of killing hundreds of kinsmen of 
the rebels in an effort to put down the invasion the deaths 
increased support for the rebels said reporters who visited the 
war zone 
the rebels in turn were accused of killing members of tribes 
seen as supporting the president in revenge for the attacks on 
their kinsmen 
government resistance stiffened when the rebels got within 35 
miles of monrovia four weeks ago 
but the rebels broke through to attack the capital in the last 
week after refusing to attend a second round of churchmediated 
peace talks aimed at ending the war 
