<TEXT>
 
i am prepared not to get nominated for the partys leading 
organs there is no need for a minister to be a member of the 
politburo presidential council and defense council 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 
my life was determined by several feelings including a feeling 
of injustice for the striking discrepancy between the proclaimed 
ideals and slogans and reality 
in the last quarter of the 20th century international 
developments are no longer determined by the struggle of two 
opposing systems that it is no longer subordinated completely 
to the dynamics of the conflict of class interests having come 
long ago to the conclusion about deadlocks into which we are pushed 
by dogmatism and ideological schemes that kill living ideas i 
actively supported and practically implemented the idea of the 
priority of human values to class group or any other interests 
i realized quite clearly that false ideology besides 
distorting goals and substituting concepts has also weight aims 
clear material incarnation 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 
i am more than convinced that our state needs strong armed 
forces but we can be armed to the teeth and live in fear ofan 
attack or you can be sure no one will attack you because policies 
can create conditions when the country will have no opponents or 
enemies 
if we continue as we did to spend onequarter of gross 
national income on military spending we will ruin the country and 
we will simply not need any defense anymore a ruined country and 
poor people do not need an army it does not make sense to defend a 
system that has led to an economic and social devastation it is up 
to politics to create security with cuts in defense expenditure 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 
is eastern europe a failure of our diplomacy yes if our 
diplomacy has never and could not set itself the aim to oppose the 
elimination in other countries of forced and alien 
administrativecommand systems totalitarian regimes even if 
events in eastern europe had not been in our interests we would 
have not interfered in their affairs we recognize not in words 
but in deeds the equality of nations sovereignty of peoples 
noninterference into their affairs their right to free choice 
any other position is chauvinism imperialism 
the fact that democratically elected leaders of our allies came 
to the meeting of the highest body of warsaw treaty organization 
does not seem a failure but an expression of respect of our 
perestroika 
we diplomats expected the changes in eastern europe but we 
could not interfere 
we forecast this we sensed that if there were not changes 
there would be tragedy 
it bitterly hurts me to see that there are people whose 
assertions lead one to believe that the soviet army didnt liberate 
some eastern european countries but all but captured them as war 
trophies chauvinistic statements insulting the dignity of 
sovereign states are permitted by some 
i see it as my moral obligation to apologize before the peoples 
of east european states for such insulting and unacceptable 
escapades on the part of my fellow countrymen 
</TEXT>
