increases 
the strike came amid heightened labor unrest organized by the 
labor partydominated histadrut labor federation following 
formation of a rightwing government in early june led by the 
rightwing likud bloc 
the previous government had included the centerleft labor party 
as the doctors launched their 24hour action electric workers 
defense industry employees and workers in other public sectors 
threatened similar action over wage disputes 
the overtime arrangement was reached in november 1988 to bypass 
complicated wage negotiations and to reduce a waiting list of tens 
of thousands of israelis needing operations and other medical care 
but the arrangement was designed to last only until march of 
this year and the government brought suit to challenge 
continuation of the system 
on thursday a tel aviv court ruled that under the law the 
overtime system could not serve as a permanent replacement for a 
wage agreement 
there are few private doctors in israel most israelis pay small 
fees for treatment in hospitals and clinics which are heavily 
subsidized by the government 
the system dates to the countrys socialist origins it has 
suffered financial difficulties in recent years because of 
inefficiency and israels wider economic troubles such as 
doubledigit inflation 
doctors basic salaries start at about 600 a month with 
overnight duty shifts adding up to several hundred dollars more to 
the wages of many attending physicians 
with the overtime payments many doctors have earned an 
additional 200 to 300 a month 
</TEXT>
