<TEXT>
a congressman called tuesday for infant 
formula makers to reduce their prices by 30 percent to prevent 
thousands of women and babies from being dropped from a 
federallyfunded feeding program 
infant formula prices have skyrocketed by nearly 150 percent in 
the last 10 years surpassing milk price increases of 364 percent 
grocery increases of 508 percent and the 591 percent rate of 
inflation said rep ron wyden dore 
the manufacturers of infant formula are gouging mothers who 
desperately need to feed their babies said wyden 
about a third of the formula sold in this country goes to 
mothers enrolled in the special supplemental feeding program for 
women infants and children 
wyden said he wrote to the chief operating officers of the five 
leading formula makers asking fr price reductions they are ross 
laboratories makers of similac mead johnson makers of enfamil 
american home products makers of sma carnation makers of great 
start and worthington foods makers of soyalac 
wyden said the two largest companies ross laboratories and mead 
johnson have raised their prices 12 times since 1981 
spokesmen at american home products the third largest infant 
formula maker and ross laboratories said they had not seen wydens 
letter and would not comment 
the letter is dated july 3 it was received this afternoon at 
about 445 pm the person to whom it was addressed is not here we 
have not read it and are not able to comment beyond that said 
jerry parrott spokesman for bristolmyers squibb co of which 
mead johnson is a subsidiary 
congress voted last week to allow states to borrow 3 percent 
against next years appropriation advocates said the move was 
necessary because rising costs of food have caused states to start 
cutting participants 
robert greenstein director of the center on budget and policy 
priorities said that even with the borrowing capacity 15 states 
will have to eliminate participants 
to be sure these states will remove significantly fewer 
participants than would have been the case if the legislation had 
not passed said greenstein however some tens of thousands 
will still be dropped perhaps as many as 100000 overall 
</TEXT>
