<TEXT>
air traffic controllers complaining they are 
overworked and underpaid began a threeday strike tuesday that 
forced cancellation of about twothirds of all flights in and out 
of paris at the start of the summer vacation season 
about 90 percent of the controllers at frances largest flight 
control center athismons south of paris reportedly joined the 
strike 
the dutch airline klm and swissair were among the foreign 
carriers that announced they were either canceling all flights into 
paris for the duration of the strike or reducing them drastically 
british airways said it canceled 14 services between heathrow 
airport and paris 
air france and the french domestic carrier air inter said they 
were reducing short and mediumhaul flights by 60 percent air 
france said it would maintain its longhaul flights 
officials warned that delays should be expected 
the strike disrupted some other flights over western europe 
because athismons controls the air space over northern france used 
on those routes 
strikers cited increased air traffic understaffing and the high 
cost of living in the paris area in demanding compensating bonuses 
in a letter to controllers transport minister michel delebarre 
expressed his profound disagreement with the strike saying it 
would seriously penalize french and foreign users and notably 
those going on vacation 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

