in luanda the capital the central committee of the ruling 
popular movement for the liberation of angola issued its statement 
after five days of often heated discussions 
the peoples republic of angola will evolve toward a 
multiparty political system within a framework of a new 
constitution to be submitted to a popular referendum the 
statement said 
but the shift away from singleparty rule would only come once 
peace stability and internal security exist it added 
the statement also reaffirmed support for president jose eduardo 
dos santos to overcome obstacles that continue to block a peace 
settlement with rebel national union for the total independence of 
angola or unita 
the rebels led by jonas savimbi have been fighting the 
government since angola gained independence from portugal in 1975 
