officials to scrap peace efforts and push further military action 
some rebel leaders have also opposed the peace talks 
after the last round of talks in midjune portuguese officials 
said the two sides were close to a lasting ceasefire agreement 
points of contention are how to monitor a ceasefire and terms 
for angolas political future diplomats said 
savimbi visiting the african nation of togo on tuesday 
demanded a ceasefire before resuming negotiations 
he said he was optimistic that talks would proceed because the 
natural allies of our antagonists are no longer in a position to 
aid them 
luanda has received massive amounts of soviet military 
equipment and moscow has pledged to continue supplies despite its 
economic problems 
the war once pitted south african forces backing unita against 
some 50000 cuban troops in angola to support the government 
