a man who was convicted six years ago 
of hacking and bludgeoning his wife and three children to death was 
granted a new trial tuesday by the illinois supreme court 
the court reversing a decision it made in 1988 ruled that 
david hendricks 1984 trial was tainted by prosecutors use of 
testimony about his alleged extramarital sexual interests 
at the trial female models employed by hendricks in his 
backbrace business testified that he fondled or kissed them while 
they were partially nude 
