de cuellar said united nations peacekeeping troops completed the 
demobilization of all but about 70 contras by thursday 
the remaining rebels were believed to have been demobilized 
since 
the report refers to both armed and unarmed rebels including 
wounded and excombatants it does not say whether family members 
were included in the figure of 21863 which seems high 
but judging by the number of rebels the report says had been 
armed 16388 it appears most of those demobilized were 
combatants 
the usbacked rebels were thought to have about 11000 
combatants and an undetermined number of support personnel in the 
last years of their war against the leftist sandinista government 
the war ended after the sandinistas were voted out of office in 
february ending their 10year rule of the central american nation 
un troops in both nicaragua and honduras where the contras 
had been based photographed the rebels then collected and 
destroyed their weapons under an agreement reached in april between 
the sandinistas the governmentelect and the rebels 
