supervision in parks is all bad 
brian suttonsmith a student of childrens play argues that 
the old games prepared children for an economy dependent on 
physical skill and strength the new ones he says train children 
for an information economy that values the manipulation of signs 
and symbols skill at a computer screen is more important than 
skill with a slingshot 
