<TEXT>
when the founders of rykodisc formed the 
small recording label in 1984 they took the name from the japanese 
word ryko meaning sound from a flash of light 
the name reflects the companys niche as a label specializing in 
compact discs which use lasers to play distortionfree digital 
recordings 
the company borrowed more than its name from the orient 
rykodiscs slogan is were only in it for the music and the 
owners stress quality over quantity 
that philosophy has made the company a minor power in the music 
industry attracting artists such as david bowie and frank zappa 
in an era of giant music conglomerates and generic packaging 
rykodisc may be the wave of the future 
we use our size to our advantage said don rose 35 one of 
the founders and partners in the company people ask us how we 
can compete with the major labels and we tell them we dont 
compete were in a position to make a bigger splash on a smaller 
scale 
rykodisc specializes in rereleasing significant titles and 
digitally remastering them when possible adding extra tracks and 
elaborate packaging the eclectic label includes rock music 
socalled world music king sunny ade hamza el din reggae folk 
and jazz 
the company is expected to gross 20 million in sales this year 
up from 4 million in 1987 
rykodisc began as a cdonly label and rode the success of cds 
business boomed and it now issues cassette tapes and lps 
the companys two biggest coups came when it acquired the 
lucrative compact disc rights to the back catalogs of frank zappa 
and david bowie rykodisc proposed deluxe reissues on cd of their 
past hits which their own record companies had neglected to do 
after two years zappa agreed to go with rykodisc since then 
more than 20 zappa cds have been issued selling more than 1 
million units and resulting in zappas first grammy and first 
international tour in years 
the company signed bowie last year after months of 
negotiations rykodiscs release of changesbowie an update of 
bowies original greatest hits collection was its first title to 
go gold 
it was a fantastic opportunity for us said rose a 
softspoken yet intense man whose office includes piles of cds 
cassettes a digital audio tape recorder dat tapes a television 
and vcr bowies stature as a innovator is really second to 
none 
in overflowing offices that overlook salem harbor rose oversees 
a staff of 15 most of whom are in their late 20s and early 30s 
the atmosphere of the companys headquarters is quiet and casual 
the walls are decorated with music posters and cd boxes 
we view ourselves as music fans and our product comes from the 
fancollector point of view said rose 
rose has telephone conferences daily with his three partners 
based in philadelphia minneapolis and los angeles 
he has been working in the music industry since the age of 18 
when he bought the first of several record stores in the midwest 
after moving to bostons north shore in 1979 he formed a small 
label called eat records 
rykodisc hopes to acquire the back catalogs of other established 
artists it also has signed new talent like australias screaming 
tribesmen in the hope of finding a breakthrough smash group that 
can make a record company 
rykodisc also founded the proenvironment ban the box 
movement calling for elimination of the elaborate 10inchlong 
boxes cds are sold in rose said the us is the only country to 
package cds that way primarily to discourage shoplifters and allow 
retailers to use their old lp shelves the ban the box movement 
advocates the sale of cds in their small cover boxes 
