forstmann little amp co plans to buy cable 
television equipment maker general instrument corp for 16 
billion in the latest sign of a mild resurgence in corporate 
buyouts 
the takeover business has been languishing in recent months 
largely due to lack of interst in junk bonds the highyield and 
highrisk securities sold to finance many of the deals of the 
1980s several recent deals however have been announced by 
companies drawing on their own cash or more conservative bank loans 
to finance the takeovers 
half the money for the general instrument buyout announced 
monday will come from forstmann littles 23 billion acquisition 
fund whose investors are mainly large corporate pension funds 
