the du pont co has begun marketing an 
herbicide designed to attack weeds that destroy corn crops 
the product accent is aimed at controlling weeds that had been 
impossible to curb shattercane johnson grass and rhizome johnson 
grass 
of the approximately 67 million acres of corn planted last year 
in the united states about 9 million acres had problems with the 
weeds don weir du pont product manager said accent could help 
cut down on farmers annual corn crop losses of 2235 million 
du pont began marketing the product in the united states on 
monday sales had been delayed pending approval from the us 
environmental protection agency which was granted friday 
weir said the herbicide is also being sold in argentina and will 
be marketed in other countries 
the herbicide is applied to corn crops after the weeds sprout 
allowing farmers to assess the extent of the weed problem before 
applying the herbicide most other herbicides are applied to the 
soil before weeds sprout 
the united states produced about 42 percent of the worlds corn 
