<DOCNO> AP900703-0255 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
here are major events in the development of the 
general motors corps saturn corp subsidiary 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
july 1982 saturn is chosen as the codename for a new gm 
smallcar project 
october 1983 gm vice president al warren and united auto 
workers union vice president donald ephlin agree to explore a new 
way to build cars in the united states 
nov 3 1983 gm chairman roger smith officially announces the 
project saying work began 18 months earlier 
dec 19 1983 ephlin and warren announce establishment of the 
gmuaw study center to look into the saturn project 
july 5 1984 thenpresident ronald reagan visits the saturn 
project housed at the gm technical center in warren mich 
sept 15 1984 the first saturn vehicle is assembled for 
testing 
jan 7 1985 gms board authorizes the formation of saturn 
corp a wholly owned gm subsidiary to produce the car joseph 
sanchez is saturns first president 
jan 8 1985 smith announces the corporations formation at a 
news conference in warren mich and shows off a running prototype 
of the car smith says the automaker would invest 5 billion in 
saturn and employ about 6000 people the original plan called for 
500000 subcompact saturn cars to be built a year 
jan 10 1985 two days after smiths announcement illinois 
gov james thompson asks gm to put the plant in his state two 
dozen governors other governors ask for the same thing 
jan 26 1985 sanchez dies at sparrow hospital in lansing mich 
feb 4 1985 william e hoglund is appointed president of 
saturn 
februaryjuly 1985 the site search goes on amid dozens of 
reports of rumors and indications of potential site selections 
july 26 1985 gm and the united auto workers union agree to a 
unique labor agreement including an elimination of job 
classifications and joint managementlabor teams 
july 30 1985 spring hill tenn is chosen as the site for the 
saturn manufacturing complex 
oct 3 1985 saturn corporate offices are dedicated in troy 
mich 
feb 3 1986 richard g lefauve succeeds hoglund as president 
of saturn corp 
april 8 1986 the plant site is formally dedicated in spring 
hill 
may 1986 spring hill site preparation begins 
oct 30 1986 gm announces it has halved the size of the 
project saying it would employ about 3000 people and produce 
about 250000 cars a year 
early 1987 construction continues at the spring hill site 
dec 7 1987 gms board approves a 19 billion for 
construction and equipment at the saturn manufacturing complex 
jan 27 1988 saturns first building the powertrain facility 
is completed but not equipped 
february 1988 saturn begins recruiting first of 3000 workers 
march 1988 first production equipment arrives at spring hill 
july 23 1988 the new spring hill city hall is completed the 
project was paid for through saturn 
mid to late1988 construction and equipping of saturn 
manufacturing buildings continues 
jan 29 1989 twentysix businesses sign saturn franchise 
agreements becoming the first dealers for the new car 
july 31 1989 saturn donates 50 acres of land for a new maury 
county tenn high school 
nov 1 1989 the first engine is produced at the saturn complex 
nov 6 1989 gms board of directors visits the spring hill 
site for the first time 
jan 13 1990 dedication of the first saturn dealership site in 
santa ana calif 
march 13 1990 first saturn dealership groundbreaking in 
memphis tenn 
spring 1990 preproduction saturn cars are assembled at the 
plant to test manufacturing systems these vehicles will be used in 
training crash testing and other research programs 
summer 1990 production of cars destined for dealers begins 
autumn 1990 saturn cars scheduled to go on sale as 1991 models 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

