the dollar rose slightly in morning trading against 
the yen tuesday while share prices on the tokyo stock exchange 
also edged upward 
the dollar started trading at 15135 yen down 005 yen from 
mondays close of 15140 yen the us currency finished the 
morning session at 152 yen with a morning low of 15132 yen 
the dollar finished at 15090 yen in new york down from 15210 
yen friday 
tsuyoshi yamamoto a dealer with the industrial bank of japan 
said shortly after the dollar opened that trading companies and 
securities firms bought the dollar to cover short positions 
the dollar then retreated slightly before posting its modest 
gain 
toru kanai of new japan securities said there wasnt much in 
the way of news to affect the dollar 
on the stock market the nikkei stock average of 225 selected 
issues rose 5937 points or 0998 percent ending the morning 
session at 3221960 the index gained 21999 points on monday and 
was up again by 32219 by the morning market close 
public works spending was the central reason for the rise 
said yoshiro inoue an analyst for nomura securities last week 
japan promised the united states to boost public works spending 
over 10 years construction and housing stocks were high as were 
industrial machinery and hightech stocks he said 
in bond dealings the price of the benchmark no 119 10year 
japanese government bonds fell slightly from mondays close of 
8653 to 8648 the yield stood at 730 percent almost unchanged 
from mondays 729 percent 
